TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=522
TASK_TITLE=Stop hook: enforce AskUserQuestion for Boss and Planner
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=0
TASK_DESCRIPTION=CATEGORY: deep
MODEL: opus

Goal: Enforce that user-facing agents (Boss + Planner) always use the AskUserQuestion tool when asking the user questions. Inline text questions get missed by users — native Claude Code TUI question UI must be used.

Scope is locked to TWO roles: Boss and Planner. Not Taskmaster, not Subtaskmaster, not Workers.

Mechanism: new Stop hook that scans the final assistant message for question patterns, checks whether AskUserQuestion was called in the same turn, and blocks the stop with feedback (exit 2) if a question was asked without the tool.

REQUIREMENTS:

1) New hook file: .claude/hooks/stop-enforce-ask-user-question.sh
   - Bash 3.2 compatible (will be linted by post-tool-lint.sh)
   - set -euo pipefail
   - Sources common.sh for init_hook + role helpers

2) Role gate — run ONLY for Boss and Planner:
   - Boss: DOEY_ROLE_ID=boss (already set by on-session-start.sh)
   - Planner: the /doey-masterplan skill spawns a Planner. VERIFY how that pane/agent is identified. Check agents/doey-planner.md and .claude/skills/doey-masterplan/ to understand how Planner runs. It may need a new DOEY_ROLE_ID=planner assignment when the masterplan window is created. If planner role isn't currently tagged in the role system, wire it in via shell/doey-roles.sh and on-session-start.sh.
   - For all other roles: exit 0 immediately.

3) Detection heuristic (tier 1 only for v1):
   - Parse the transcript JSONL (.claude/projects/<slug>/<session>.jsonl)
   - Extract the last assistant message text
   - Strip fenced code blocks (), inline code (), quoted blocks (> ...), and markdown headers (^#+ )
   - Check the last non-empty line of the stripped text
   - If it ends with '?' AND starts with a second-person trigger (case-insensitive, after trimming leading bullets/dashes):
     * Should I
     * Do you
     * Would you
     * Which
     * Can you / Can I
     * Want me to
     * Or (as conjunction-question)
   - → that's a violation

4) Tool-call check:
   - In the same turn (from the last 'user' entry forward), parse tool_use events in the transcript
   - If AskUserQuestion was called → pass (not a violation)
   - If detected violation AND tool NOT called → block

5) Block behavior (exit 2 with stderr feedback):
   Message:
   BLOCKED: Your response ends with a question to the user, but you didn't call AskUserQuestion.
   Questions to users MUST use the AskUserQuestion tool so they render in the native Claude Code UI. Plain-text questions get missed.
   Detected pattern: "<excerpt of the offending line>"
   Action: Retry your response. Keep the explanation text, but replace the question with an AskUserQuestion tool call. You may ask up to 4 questions per call, with 2-4 options per question.

6) Shadow mode (MANDATORY — do not ship blocking on day 1):
   - Env var: DOEY_ENFORCE_QUESTIONS with values shadow|block|off
   - Default: shadow
   - shadow: detect violations, append to .doey/violations/ask-user-question.jsonl, do NOT block
   - block: detect + actively block via exit 2
   - off: skip hook entirely
   - Violation log format: one JSON object per line with {ts, role, session, excerpt, tier}

7) Retry cap:
   - When in block mode, if the same pane is blocked twice in a row for this rule, log a 'retry_cap_hit' event and allow through on the third try with a warning. Prevents infinite loops.
   - Track via a small counter file in /tmp/doey/<session>/enforce-retry-<pane>.count, cleared on successful non-violating response.

8) Settings wiring:
   - Register the new hook in the appropriate hook loader (check how existing stop-*.sh hooks are wired — probably via .claude/settings.json or install.sh)
   - Fresh install compatible: DOEY_ENFORCE_QUESTIONS=shadow must be the default after curl|bash, with no manual setup
   - Document in docs/ and in agents/doey-boss.md + agents/doey-planner.md (pointer to the rule)

9) Testing:
   - tests/test-bash-compat.sh must pass
   - Add a unit test or E2E scenario: Boss responds with 'Should I proceed?' in shadow mode → .doey/violations/ask-user-question.jsonl entry written, no block. Same in block mode → exit 2 + feedback in stderr.
   - Verify Planner role detection works when /doey-masterplan is invoked — create a Planner window, have it emit a test response with a question, confirm the hook fires.

10) Rollout plan (ship, then tune):
    - Ship with DOEY_ENFORCE_QUESTIONS=shadow
    - After 3 real sessions, review .doey/violations/ask-user-question.jsonl for false positives
    - Tune heuristic if needed (tier 1 patterns)
    - Flip default to 'block' in a follow-up task
    - DO NOT flip to block in this task — shadow only for the first ship

CONSTRAINTS:
- Bash 3.2 compatible (no associative arrays, no mapfile, etc.)
- Respect fresh-install invariant
- No new dependencies
- One worker per file (this should be single-worker scope anyway)

DELIVERABLES:
- .claude/hooks/stop-enforce-ask-user-question.sh
- Role wiring for Planner if needed (shell/doey-roles.sh, on-session-start.sh)
- Settings registration (.claude/settings.json or install.sh update)
- Violation log directory creation
- Unit/E2E test
- docs/enforce-ask-user-question.md explaining the rule, env var, shadow mode, and how to tune
- Updated agents/doey-boss.md and agents/doey-planner.md with rule pointer

Plan first — this is PLANNED because: (a) requires investigating how Planner is identified today, (b) touches hook loader + role system + agent definitions, (c) has a shadow→block rollout strategy. Interview/research phase should verify Planner role identification BEFORE writing the hook.
